description:
The proposed work involves migrating approximately 800 to 1000 pipelines from the Azure (Synapse) environment to Databricks on GCP, following the medallion architecture (Bronze, Silver, and Gold).

The migration will be performed in an "As Is" format, meaning a clean replication of the same queries from Synapse to Databricks, using the structure already created by one of our analysts, organized into notebooks and scheduled via workflows for daily loads.

Databricks was deployed in the PRJ-INGEST√ÉO-DE-DADOS-BI project, utilizing the shared network PRJ-HOST-NETWORK to align with security policies.

A cluster was created with a cost-effective configuration, ensuring optimization without compromising data ingestion pipeline processing capacity, along with the installation of the JDBC library.

The Bronze, Silver, and Gold layers were structured in Google Cloud Storage, ensuring organization, modularity, and scalability of the environment.

With the infrastructure set up, the project will move forward with implementing data ingestion pipelines while maintaining the logic, queries, and business rules from Azure.  

Additionally, the resource must clone the Power BI dashboards currently hosted in Microsoft's Azure cloud and upload them to the designated workspace for dashboards in GCP.

Once migrated, the data sources within the dashboards must be repointed to Databricks, ensuring that all dashboards function seamlessly with the new data infrastructure.

The goal of the project is to migrate all the pipelines and have cloned dashboards in perfect condition, identical to the production environment.  

The code structure includes:

extracting data from the Bronze layer (tables such as *[REDACTED], *[REDACTED]*, and *[REDACTED]**, consolidated via UNION ALL);

type conversion and column creation (e.g., CD_ATENDIMENTO converted to DOUBLE, CD_SERVICO converted to DECIMAL (38,0), DS_TIP_MAR converted to STRING);

creation of surrogate keys to ensure uniqueness and traceability (such as SK_FATO_ATENDIMENTO, SK_FATO_PACIENTE, SK_ESPECIALID, SK_CONVENIO, SK_CID, SK_LEITOS, SK_ORI_ATE, and SK_PRESTADOR);

data enrichment by adding a DATA_CARGA column (formatted as dd/MM/yyyy);

column selection to include the created surrogate keys and relevant attributes;

saving transformed data in the Silver layer via saveTableFileSilver ("DIM_ATENDIMENTO", df);

saving validated data in the Gold layer using saveTableFileGold ("lwd_dim_atendimento_01", df);

and data visualization by loading a Parquet file for validation and display.  

This ETL process is designed to consolidate data from multiple sources into the Bronze layer, enrich it in the Silver layer, and make it available in the Gold layer for advanced analytics.

Databricks Workflows will be used to orchestrate task execution, allowing flexible automation and integration with other systems.

The detailed workflow functionality includes adding tasks, where each step represents a phase in the pipeline, ensuring an efficient automation process for data migration, transformation, and dashboard replication.
